						               													<description>About: In Cyber Siege everyone is a hacker trying to gain control of the system through use of programs, once you have uploaded or install all your bytes of data to the system you have taken control. Cyber Siege is a game that uses temporary alliances, strategy, and program actions to advance your own agenda, or slow down your opponents. Discussion, deals, persuasion, and even temporary treaties are allowed and encouraged. Turns are fast in this game and everyone stays engages the whole game. The rules are simple to understand but there is still strategic depth. Players will attempt to take control of Programs by installing more bytes of data then their opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory Condition: Be the first player to Upload or Install all your bytes of data from your hard drive into the System!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Play: &amp;#10;Cyber Siege consists of several game rounds separated into three phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Install Phase: Players take turns installing bytes of data into one of many programs in order to take majority control and take the programs action.&amp;#10;     Execution Phase: Players take turns executing programs. Each program has a special ability that either helps yourself or hurts one of your opponents. But because the scoring is hidden no one knows for sure who is winning, therefor deflection and collusion to change who to attack is an open table discussion.&amp;#10;     Packet Generation Phase: Players simultaneously generate there data packet (the number of bytes of data they will get to install on the following round) based upon the actions executed by the program.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
